Classes in suncertify.db.dao used by suncertify.db.dao
ComparisonOperator
          ComparisonOperator is a simple enum class containing comparison operators.
DaoDuplicateException
          DaoDuplicateException is thrown when user tries to store/update record(s) with not unique data (i.e. record with the same data already exists in database).
DaoException
          DaoException is thrown when general failure connected with DAO operations occurs and is also base class for all specific exceptions that can occur during DAO proceedings.
DaoFinderException
          DaoFinderException is thrown when finder/loader methods could not find required objects in the persistent layer.
DaoStaleObjectException
          DaoStaleObjectException is thrown when user wants to perform DAO operation on the stale data (e.g. user wants to update the record no longer exists).
IDao
          IDao interface consists of common Data Access Object methods for CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete).
